The food is immaculate. So delicious and the service is always amazing. Best authentic African cuisine in Brooklyn.
Jesus Christ the food here is so radiant, flavorful, and authentic! I just moved to the neighborhood and this is definitely my favorite spot. Thank you!
Nasty food, no favor, the food was super spicy and cold. Taste like it was microwaved so not fresh cooked food. Expensive fo no reason. I don't recommend this place at all save ur money.

I ordered an egusi soup.. and it was spoiled!! The smell was out this world when I open the food! I already knew when I taste it,it  was going  to taste exactly how it smelled.  and it did!! I let others taste it to see if it was just me and it wasn't!! like as if they had it sitting there for days..
Great customer service.  The food is amazing
They don’t keep to their deal. When they say buy one get one free, you buy one and they don’t give the other one. I have had at least 3 issues with my orders. Would not be patronizing them again.

Definitely a dope spot you should give a try!! The people here are nice and friendly and very informative if you are not sure what to get. I 100% recommend the  trying there version of fufu it’s amazing! You see me back there more often!
West African Take out Bushwick. Pickup

Not the best Jollof I ever had. It is very spicy otherwise i taste the tomato paste. I asked that the fish be put to the side but it came in the same dish as the rice. I don't like gravy on my rice and i'm just glad it wasn't all over. I probably won't be ordering again but the food wasn't horrible.

I had gone to a previous restaurant and had a very bad experience and just searched and found this , I decided to try it out. Ordered Afang soup and pounded yam. OMG!!!  It’s like someone took me back home. Very tasty, it’s going to be my go to place from now on.

I ordered take out recently and I really enjoyed the meal. It was deliciously cooked and well packed. I will definitely order from them again and again. Most tasty African restaurant in the neighborhood hands down.
Excellent service super friendly & their food was delicious!!!
Delicious! Chicken with jollof rice and plantain was excellent. Staff was very kind and helpful.
The food was so delicious and the service impeccable. Highly recommend!
Jollof rice with fish, plantains, and a side of spinach. Very spicey and yummy! Lives up to the NYT review. Hillary was a very nice host!!

My son took me here. He was so full of praise for this restaurant because he always ordered through UberEat. It wasn't disappointing at all. The server, Promise, was very friendly and knowledgeable in what she does. I ordered Afang soup with pounded yam, Calabar style, it tasted just like my mama used to make in Calabar. The food was so good that I ordered 2 Egusi and jollof rice to go for my wife and children at home. They are very pleasant to deal with, I wasn't surprised to see lots of American whites eating in there because that's the place to eat real Nigerian food. Go there and you too will be convinced.
MY GOD DIS PLACE IS SO GOOD... STEW TASTE LIKE BACK HOME 🇳🇬 AND DA EGUSI IS PERFECT. ❤️ Am coming back confirmed

We ordered take-out, it was so good! Very tasty african food, pretty spicy though - if you don't like it hot, this place is maybe not for you. Even still, I recommend anyone to give it a try, simply because it was so damn tasty! Will order again, loved the jollof rice.
I live on the block and eat here all the time. When the jalloof is fresh, it's hard to beat. The fish pepper soup is a revelation.
Uuff, the yollof rice with stock fish is delicious. I went there for the first time after the pandemic and Ive been eating there ever since. Five stars for sure.

I went here with my sister for African food and it was AMAZING! It reminded us of home, their staff is super nice and they are very clean. the gentleman who served us was super friendly! We even asked to see the lady who cooked it coz WOW! We defenetly recommend it. It  defenetly felt like home away from home.
The Egusi and Goat with mashed Yam was AMAZING. I live very close to this place and wish I went in sooner.

Firstly I ordered based on the amazing reviews everywhere.  The moin moin was soggy and just bland. I threw that out. The buka stew was just not nice.  The goat pepper soup was ayt, so was the afang even though it wasn't authentic afang made more so in an efo riro style/ vegetable and stew on the side type. I have never known afang to be made with stew or eaten with stew on the side.  Pretty much my whole order was a waste and I was still hungry after it all.

I ordered from here for the first time yesterday & I’m about to place another order right now ! Lol. This is THE BEST African food I’ve had & I’ve tried multiple places. It taste fresh , flavorful , the right amount of spice , good portion size for the price. I love this place !!! Thank you Hills Kitchen. You’re the bomb !
Delicious food. You can taste the care and quality of ingredients that go into the preparation of your meal. Can’t wait to try more things from the menu.

Fish pepper soup and jollof ..mad!🙏🏾💜  Update: been back here probably more than a dozen times in the last 4 months, since my first visit. Food is still amazing! Jollof, moi moi, plaintain always the best picked it seems, fried rice, zobo.. all mad!  And they should definitely charge more!🤤  And promise is an angel! Love going to say hi
The jollof w beef is DELICIOUS!!!!!! Great stafff!!! So nice
Food taste delicious and clean. Service was customer-centric. Definitely going back for more.
Best African food around the area
The food here was very good. I recommended coming here. The Egusi soup is really good.

The Staff was extremely nice, ( and Handsome 😏) It was my first time there, I asked for recommendations & they guided me through what’s best on the menu! Also, who can’t resist a meat pie!? Food was very good, I made it into 2 meals because it’s so filling! I will be back, Definitely recommend!
This place is freakin AMAZING. Everything we got was just mind blowingly good. And HUGE portions! Def will be ordering here again

Disappointing. Goat was tough AF, plantains were mushy, greens were greasy.  I asked for mild (sadly, I have a stomach issue where spicy food is no bueno right now) and it was extremely spicy. In the end, we had to throw away most of the food.  Wanted to love it, but we will not return.
Very good
Love this spot! Great food and great service. Highly recommend the jollof rice with chicken. Also the fried plantains are delicious.
Best place in brooklyn. I got promise and Hilary who were absolutely amazing. I can’t wait to go back

I found this gem and have not stopped coming! They're food is flavor-filled, bot many restaurants I can say that about. The spinach with the fish, excellent. Love, love, love, the jollof rice. I would recommend this place to any and all. But, don't take my word, I would suggest you simply give it try, you will not regret it!
Neat environment.  Their food are so delicious, good consumers service.
Alright.
Good
Wow - the red sauce in which the goat was cook was unreal. Kind /friendly service.
This is a great restaurant to be I enjoyed my meal and love there service

Great kitchen....Made me to be at home while am visiting new York. Now I don't need to worry about my African delicacies since Hills kitchen is around.  You need to have the experience of the real jollof rice. Still smiling.
The best Nigerian restaurant in Brooklyn. If you’re ever in the area you have to stop by and indulge. Server was very nice and prompt. Food came out great.
The food was delicious nice place and overall great service! ❤️
Very well prepared and delicious. I will surely come back again.

Nigerian food in Bushwick. ⚡️⚡️⚡️🇳🇬Brooklyn is such a special place and if you haven’t had African food other than Ethiopian, you are in for a beautiful cuisine. This kitchen is as if my mom was here and that is something I appreciate. This will become my second living room.  If you order food to go, that is on you. Our culture is meant to be eaten in house, and then taken away. It just isn’t fast food.
The owner is super hott! Chef is authentic African female cook, very comforting!

CoZy spot with overly nice staff which its hard to find this days. I ordered egusi with beef, came fast to my table, good proportions of food with great taste. For the money and attention i loved the experience of trying something different to my regular diet.

I visited Hills Kitchen with a friend visiting from out of town. It was a quiet weekend afternoon. The proprietors/managers Promise and Hillary (the really athletic bloke) were exceptionally friendly.  The food arrived right on time, and Hillary was happy to answer all questions about his spot. After "handling" the Egusi in house, me and my friend decided we had to each order a buncb of side dishes to go. The Egusi, pepper soup and Ukazi wherre on point.
I'm an African.... So i understand how our food tastes like, I'm really into Hills kitchen food, It's amazing experience everytime , Thanks y'all for given us home away from Africa.
Great customer service great food👍

This is the newest Nigerian Restaurant in the NYC area. I must say they are off to a great start! The restaurant was very clean nice and cozy (very good for dine in). They offer take home options also. The staff were very friendly, attentive and swift. (For a Nigerian restaurant the service was super quick).  NOW THE FOOD: AMAZING!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! they offer a vast variety of Nigerian cuisines especially the exotic soups and stews. I was very impressed with the food and the size portions were very decent (I couldn't finish my meal).  Overall, I'll highly recommend anyone looking for good Nigerian food in the NYC area to visit!
Food was on point, nice to sit in, friendly service.
The foods and customer service is wonderful, I ate the native vegetable soup with poundo yam, and I did not regret it, it was the best...Africans should try it and thank me later

I loved the food and and service. The woman who served me and my partner gave me that west African woman look  that they give to those of us born 400 years away from Africa  ... you know the look ... that we should  know... and we should!!!  The food is strangely familiar and wonderfully new like the first time you heard Fela Kuti.  She even sat a water bowl next to me and said " you know what to do with this."  There was no question in her voice...I hand to eat with my hand  -  the right hand of course!!  I had the white soup with pounded yam and  my Dominican partner had jolof rice with beef and plantains ( of course!!! --- Dominicans are undercover Africans ).  That night  I dreamed of the food - really.  I did.  But be careful it can be spicy in a way that is different than Mexican hot.. Like Fela's music  you need to give your body time to catch up with you soul. FOR THOSE WHO HAVE NO IDEA WHAT I AM TALKING ABOUT visit before you order online  and ask for a suggestion.  Remember  almost all the dishes have cured fish in it . it's an essential spice like fish sauce in Thai food. Finally -The West African approach to beef  is different from  European and Asian cuisine.   It's served with more texture (  some   might call it "tough") and very well done. Again  like Fela's music you need to give your body time to catch your soul.
Ordered the white rice with steak stew via Seamless. Good flavor and rice was fine, but the steak was dry and very tough. Very oily, too. Called it quits after 3 bites.
Absolutely wonderful.. On a par with Whitehouse Jollof Rice, Sabo Yaba! Party stew.. Super tasty.. All too nice..👍👍👍
I ordered the joloff rice with goat. Superb. “Wow... that was great” sighed my boyfriend a little while after eating. Swift, generous proportions.
Very nice food, and very friendly staff. 100% recommended!

Excellent customer service. Food is normally prepared swiftly and delivered promptly. I've become a repeat customer for their authentic Nigerian beans. Today they went out of their way to fix an issue I had with an order and I really appreciate the service and efforts made to rectify it. I recommended them to my friend who has fallen in love with their beans too!
They have the best jollof rice in all of Brooklyn. I have tried so many African restaurants here and theirs have that authentic taste of home with real Nigerian spices 😋😋!

The food was absolutely delicious, service was attentive and swift. Everything we ate, we all had different fufu with stew (no jollof rice), tasted fresh. If you like your food spicy make sure to tell them so they can increase the heat. When we were there we were the only customers, but they didn't hover. All in all I would go back anytime.
As a tipical  African guy. It's home away from home. You never know until you stop by.
Great food,will come back again
Awesome food! Spicy and tasty, really a treasure!
Amazing food! Cool people!
Excellent cuisine, nicely surprised. Very good Nigerian food  Update: I kept ordering from them and really no disappointment, the food is always fresh and very traditional. Great place!!
Wonderful!
The best Nigerian food in New York City!!!🙏🏽👍🏼💪🏽
The food was great.  The prices aren’t bad either. Great staff also.  Try the zobo!

The best place on earth. First time having African and I’m literally in love and I’m full lol and I have lunch for tomorrow bc the portion is so big lol. Totally worth it in every way. I can’t wait to tell all my friends in the area
Great restaurant and ambiance. The chef and staff are very friendly and the food is AMAZING. Very flavorful and authentic West African dishes. I highly recommend this place.
Shining, warm energy, tasty, mellifluous flavors. Adds a good and welcomed spirit to the neighborhood. Absolutely will come again.  Recommends: Edikaikong
Had the white soup, 100% recommended!
I ordered egusi and pounded yam. It was very tasty. The tripes though 😍😍😍 Portion is good if you’re really hungry. Got knocked out after eating. Highly recommended
I had the jollof rice and fish! It was so good, I'll be back! :)
Excellent customer service and delicious food!!! Glad I stumbled upon this place!!!!
Her food is delicious and authentic. I paid for a $35 uber ride just to go eat there again.
Good food.
Amazing food!  Truly great find
Food is great!! Staff is nice.
Amazing laid back and friendly environment with Tasty, delicious food.

Nice and clean restaurant. Reasonable prices, with good customer service. Actually, one of the best West African restaurants in the center of Brooklyn - New York City. I really do enjoyed the food from here in my two days stay in NY. 👌👌👌

Visited Hills kitchen on the new opening and the warm welcome and greeting I got made me feel really  welcome the staff was polite and pleasant the food was delicious great Presentation and the style I would recommend Hills kitchen anytime come and join and have a great  experience
Hills kitchen is very cozy, welcoming and feels just like home. Jollof rice was super. I enjoyed every bit of it. Staff very pleasant and restaurant clean.

Very warm and cozy ambience, friendly staff with excellent customer service.  The food is value for money, well portioned for pricing which Is very affordable considering the very Original Nigerian cuisines served. Very great for that birthday party and or group hangout.

Very happy we learned about this fabulous restaurant that looks right onto a park. By chance, we arrived on the opening day and everything seemed to be working well. There are a number of menu choices, but our charming server, Favor, helped us pick the jollof rice with beef and plantains. We ordered it with a little extra spice and the heat was just right. Looking forward to our next visit to try some of the other choices. Nice addition to the neighborhood!

Was in the Bushwick area when I discovered this place and was pleasantly surprised to find an African restaurant in the area. Naturally I had to stop in for a bite. The service was wonderful, I didn’t have to wait too long for my food and the food itself was exquisite. Will definitely be coming back for more.
